Shinshu Mars distillery is a Japanese whisky distillery founded in 1985 and located at Miyada, Kyushu island, Japan.

At around 2,600 ft above sea level, Shinshu Mars distillery is Japan’s highest whisky distillery.

node.text:
Made from spirit aged in four types of barrels, this Laphroaig is a complex and full-bodied dram.

Partly aged in new American oak, rarely used in Scotch whisky production, this dram has beautiful notes of peat smoke, stewed fruit and toasted vanilla.

P.

📸 : @brutdefut

node.text:
Named after the ancient stone used for British Royal coronation ceremonies for centuries, symbolizing the approval for the incoming king, this Royal Salute from Chivas has matured for a minimum of 38 years.

King George V celebrates the first Royal Warrant granted to John Walker and Sons Ltd to supply Scotch whisky to the British Royal Household in 1934, and is apparently designed to recreate how JW might have tasted back in the day. Some Port Ellen has been used, alongside Cardhu, Lochnagar and some very old grain whisky

Two royal drams paying tribute to amazing knowledge and tradition.

📸 : @caledoniawhiskyco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whisky Nation 🔥 in Paris, France. May be an image of bottle.

node.text:
Samaroli is an Italian independent bottling company, with a focus on bottling exceptional Scotch whisky and Caribbean rums; Samaroli does not own any distilleries. The company was founded by the late Silvano Samaroli in Rome in 1968, and was one of the first dedicated bottlers to actively promote cask strength whisky. The first series, a set of Cadenhead bottlings, was released in 1979.

During the early 1980s Samaroli began to source more individual releases directly from Cadenhead, and more cask strength bottlings started to appear. In 2008 the day-to-day running of the company was taken over from Silvan Samaroli by Antonio Bleve.

Samaroli holds the belief that independent bottlers should add their own value, and they ensure this through re-casking their whisky into virgin oak casks to add individuality. The striking artistry of their labels is iconic, straying far from traditional whisky labels, with the much-loved line on the rear labels: ‘Further matures in its bottle’.

Source : Master Of Malt
📸: : @whiskyauctioneer

node.text:
This 30 years old Bowmore has been distilled in 1989 and is the result of the vatting of sherry hogsheads and bourbon barrels bottled at cask strength 45,3%.⁣

With 2 580 bottles available this bottling is inspired by the terrain that surrounds the Bowmore distillery.⁣

📸 : @taraspirits
